SIMPLE: octroi
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Octroi
<hw>Oc`troi"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A privilege granted by the sovereign authority, as the
exclusive right of trade granted to a guild or society; a
concession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tax levied in money or kind at the gate of a
French city on articles brought within the walls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><altsp>[Written also <asp>octroy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Octuor</ent>⟦br⟧
